==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kaoline
<hw>Ka"o*line</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Chin. <ets>kao-ling</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A very pure white clay, ordinarily in the form of an impalpable
powder, and used to form the paste of porcelain; China clay; porcelain
clay. It is chiefly derived from the decomposition of common
feldspar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name is now applied to all porcelain clays which
endure the fire without discoloration.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kaolinization</ent>⟦br⟧
